	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Problem is that Casino's buy their card decks pre-shuffled and consisting of several decks of cards. The shuffling before shipment is done by a machine. This machine shuffles the cards in certian amounts from the start set, that having a good memory and recognizing patterns, you can guess the chance of the next card in this pattern within a margin of +/- 4 cards. Add to that the ability to remember what cards are already played and you can make a fair guess on what card will be next.<br />
<br />
Of course you need a very adaptive brain to figure this out and still remember it, but some people are just good at recognizing patterns.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
